Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner stuffed
Over one third of children aged between 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and 5% obesity.
Obese children come from most families with an unhealthy lifestyle, as is the case with current research.
The importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as reference, is demonstrated again.
At the table, obsessive children, for example, are fed of embuty at least twice as often as children of normal weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had eaten fries the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence".
In overweight families there is no habit of sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of the last year of school and participated in the same nearly 900 basic education children from all over Czechia.
It was already the second edition of the program of "Obesity of Not a Accident", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
A proper diet and exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly decrease the number of children with overweight and even obesity.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five daily meals according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," one of the survey's results.
No breakfast but with ink for dinner
Experts warn that, in a healthy development, details are also important, such as having a set time for family breakfast.
In Czechia, however, only 23 per cent of school families are having breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one has breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10 per cent of the homes there is no breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that the families of obese children are much more often consumed with sick fries.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink daily sweet soft drinks (70%).
Usually they do more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled selected boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children between 12 and 15 years of age, from the point of view of healthy diet, are far from ideal."
Among its favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is especially alarming the popularity of sweet soft drinks," the final report of the study warns.
As the main food, the pasta is taken away and the poultry meat is closely followed by it.
Practically, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who completed the questionnaire after the end of the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence," in many cases an important change was made in favour of the principles of healthy diet," points to the results of the study.
Call attention, for example, to the matter of soft drinks, where many children would begin to prefer normal and common water.
Children would also choose poultry meat and fish for main food more frequently in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
