The innovative IBM begins its second century of existence
If someone was looking for a term that would define the IBM strategy very precisely, the approximate one would be "long term".
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and, however, has already been 100 years since its foundation.
The foundation of this long-lasting character was laid by the first head of the signature, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He has already coined the motto that many problems in the world have a solution if people are willing to think.
