This is a measure that could raise a wave of anger, but which would save 280 million euros, according to Les Echos.
In addition, it would be accompanied by another measure with a more symbolic scope: to impose on officials a day of non-remuneration in the event of a job loss (up to now, they have no shortage, compared to the three days applied in the private sector).
While these issues are being discussed, the majority of them also put on the table the issue of fraud, this time geared towards the abuse of labour casualties.
